						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the outer <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Durgā-Paramēśvari temple.</p>						

						<p>Mallikārjuna, 1451 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers a gift of land to the goddess Durgā Paramēśvarī of Uppunda by <hi rend="bold">Bhānappa-voḍeya</hi> who was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya</hi> under the orders of <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Va[lla]bhadaṇṇāyaka.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1374, Prajōtpatya, Kārttika śu. 5, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1451 A.D., October 31.</hi> The weekday, however was Saturday.</p>						

						</summary>
